{"questionId":"22513230","questionHtml":"<p>Show that <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>AB</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>28</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>57</mn></math>, correct to four significant figures.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p><strong>METHOD 1</strong></p>\n<p>let <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">M</mi></math> be the midpoint of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced open=\"[\" close=\"]\"><mi>AB</mi></mfenced></math> and so <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>AB</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>AM</mi></math></p>\n<p>attempts to use Pythagoras’ theorem to find&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>AM</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></math>&nbsp; &nbsp;OR&nbsp; &nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>AM</mi></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>AM</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>=</mo><msup><mn>20</mn><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><msup><mn>14</mn><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfenced><mrow><mo>=</mo><mn>204</mn></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp;OR&nbsp; &nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>AM</mi><mo>=</mo><msqrt><msup><mn>20</mn><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><msup><mn>14</mn><mn>2</mn></msup></msqrt><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfenced><mrow><mo>=</mo><mn>14</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>2828</mn><mo>…</mo><mo>=</mo><msqrt><mn>204</mn></msqrt><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><msqrt><mn>51</mn></msqrt></mrow></mfenced></math></p>\n<p>recognizes that&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>AB</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>AM</mi></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>AB</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>×</mo><mn>14</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>2828</mn><mo>…</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfenced><mrow><mo>=</mo><mn>28</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>5657</mn><mo>…</mo></mrow></mfenced><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfenced><mrow><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><msqrt><mn>204</mn></msqrt><mo>=</mo><mn>4</mn><msqrt><mn>51</mn></msqrt></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>AB</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>28</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>5657</mn><mo>…</mo></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>AB</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>28</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>57</mn></math> (m)&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>AG</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>METHOD 2</strong></p>\n<p>let <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">M</mi></math> be the midpoint of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced open=\"[\" close=\"]\"><mi>AB</mi></mfenced></math> and so <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>AB</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>AM</mi></math></p>\n<p>let&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>θ</mi><mo>=</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi><mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">S</mi><mo>^</mo></mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">M</mi></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>θ</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>795398</mn><mo>…</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfenced><mrow><mo>=</mo><msup><mi>cos</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup><mo> </mo><mfrac><mn>14</mn><mn>20</mn></mfrac></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>attempts to use a valid trigonometric ratio&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>EITHER</strong></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>AM</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>14</mn><mi>tan</mi><mo> </mo><mfenced><mrow><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>795398</mn><mo>…</mo></mrow></mfenced><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfenced><mrow><mo>=</mo><mn>14</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>2828</mn><mo>…</mo><mo>=</mo><mn>14</mn><mi>tan</mi><mo> </mo><mfenced><mrow><msup><mi>cos</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup><mo> </mo><mfrac><mn>14</mn><mn>20</mn></mfrac></mrow></mfenced></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><strong>OR</strong></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>AM</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>20</mn><mo> </mo><mi>sin</mi><mo> </mo><mfenced><mrow><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>795398</mn><mo>…</mo></mrow></mfenced><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfenced><mrow><mo>=</mo><mn>14</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>2828</mn><mo>…</mo><mo>=</mo><mn>20</mn><mo> </mo><mi>sin</mi><mo> </mo><mfenced><mrow><msup><mi>cos</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup><mo> </mo><mfrac><mn>14</mn><mn>20</mn></mfrac></mrow></mfenced></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><strong>THEN</strong></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>AB</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>28</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>5657</mn><mo>…</mo></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>AB</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>28</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>57</mn></math> (m)&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>AG</strong></em></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:right;\"><em><strong>[3 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"22513230","referenceCode":"24M.2.AHL.TZ2.11a","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"Show that AB=28.57, correct to four significant figures.","paper":"2","level":"AHL","questionNumber":"a","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 3]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 3— Geometry and trigonometry","Prior learning","Topic 3— Geometry and trigonometry","SL 3.3—Applications: angles of elevation and depression, bearings"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}}}